# E-Griverence Codebase Analysis
*University E-Grievance Hub — Full-Stack Web Application*

---

## 1. Project Overview

E-Griverence is a **university grievance management platform** that allows students to file, track, and follow up on complaints, while admins (department-level) and a super admin manage, resolve, and escalate those grievances. It is a production-grade full-stack application built with Node.js + Express + MongoDB on the backend and React + Vite on the frontend.

**Three portals, one codebase:**
| Portal | Role | Access Path |
|---|---|---|
| Student Portal | `student` | `/`, `/login`, `/signup`, `/dashboard` |
| Department Admin | `admin` | `/admin`, `/admin/login`, `/admin/dashboard` |
| Super Admin | `superadmin` | `/superadmin`, `/superadmin/login`, `/superadmin/dashboard` |

---

## 2. Monorepo Layout

```
E-Griverence/
├── backend/               # Node.js / Express API server
│   ├── server.js          # Entry point
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── Database/      # MongoDB connection
│   │   ├── controllers/   # Route handler logic
│   │   ├── models/        # Mongoose schemas (15 models)
│   │   ├── routes/        # Express routers (15 route files)
│   │   ├── middleware/     # Auth, RBAC, rate limiting, uploads, error handling
│   │   ├── jobs/          # Background cron jobs
│   │   ├── utils/         # Cache, email, OTP, ID generators
│   │   ├── seed/          # DB seed scripts
│   │   └── constants/     # Shared constants
│   ├── uploads/           # Uploaded files (grievance attachments, ID cards, landing images)
│   └── package.json
├── frontend/              # React + Vite SPA
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── App.jsx / main.jsx
│   │   ├── api/           # Axios instance (HTTP client)
│   │   ├── context/       # React Context (Auth, Notification)
│   │   ├── hooks/         # Custom hooks (useBranding, useNotifications)
│   │   ├── components/    # Reusable UI (common, ui, landing, protected)
│   │   ├── pages/         # Route-level pages (Admin, User, SuperAdmin, Auth, Landing, Shared)
│   │   ├── routes/        # AppRoutes.jsx — React Router config
│   │   └── styles/        # Additional CSS
│   └── package.json
├── docker-compose.yml     # 4-service Docker stack
├── DESIGN.md              # Comprehensive design document
└── ecosystem.config.cjs   # PM2 config
```

---

## 3. Backend — Deep Dive

### 3.1 Entry Point (`server.js`)

The server startup sequence:
1. **Env validation** — fails fast if `MONGODB_URL`, `ACCESS_TOKEN_SECRET`, or `REFRESH_TOKEN_SECRET` are missing/too short
2. **Middleware stack** — Helmet (CSP in prod), compression, CORS, CSRF guard (prod-only), JSON/urlencoded body parsers, cookie-parser, mongo-sanitize (NoSQL injection), hpp (HTTP parameter pollution)
3. **Static file serving** — `/uploads/landing/*` is public; all other `/uploads/` paths require `authenticate` middleware
4. **Health endpoints** — `GET /api/health` and `GET /api/ready`
5. **15 route groups** mounted under `/api/*`
6. **Graceful shutdown** — SIGTERM/SIGINT/uncaughtException all close HTTP server then Mongoose connection

### 3.2 Route Map

| Prefix | File | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `/api/auth` | `authRoutes.js` | Login/register/refresh/logout/OTP (15 KB) |
| `/api/grievances` | `grievanceRoutes.js` | Core grievance CRUD + comments + attachments (33 KB — largest file) |
| `/api/superadmin` | `superAdminRoutes.js` | Admin management, platform config (32 KB) |
| `/api/admin` | `adminRoutes.js` | Dept-scoped grievance ops |
| `/api/users` | `userRoutes.js` | Student profile management |
| `/api/students` | `studentRoutes.js` | Student-specific endpoints |
| `/api/departments` | `departmentRoutes.js` | Department CRUD |
| `/api/courses` | `courseRoutes.js` | Course CRUD |
| `/api/categories` | `categoryRoutes.js` | Grievance category management |
| `/api/notifications` | `notificationRoutes.js` | In-app notifications |
| `/api/audit-logs` | `auditLogRoutes.js` | Tamper-evident audit trail |
| `/api/reports` | `reportRoutes.js` | CSV/PDF report generation |
| `/api/site` | `siteRoutes.js` | Global site settings |
| `/api/landing-config` | `landingConfigRoutes.js` | Landing page editor |
| `/api/categories` | `complaintTypeRoutes.js` | Legacy complaint type endpoint |

### 3.3 Data Models (15 Mongoose schemas)

| Model | Purpose |
|---|---|
| **User** | Unified user document for students, admins, and superadmins. Has password hashing (bcrypt, 12 rounds), session tracking (`activeSessions[]`), step-up auth fields, lock/rate-limit fields, and a virtual `currentYear` derived from `admissionYear`. |
| **Admin** | **Legacy** schema — kept for backward compat with pre-migration seeded admins. Auth middleware falls back to this if the primary `User` lookup fails. Uses email validation restricted to `.ac.in` domains. |
| **Grievance** | Core entity. 6 statuses (Pending → InProgress → UnderReview → Resolved/Closed → Escalated), 4 priorities. Embedded `timeline[]`, `comments[]`, `attachments[]` sub-documents. SLA deadline field + reopen workflow fields. Race-condition-safe atomic `grievanceId` via pre-validate hook. |
| **GrievanceCategory** | Categories for grievances (Academic, Hostel, etc.) |
| **Department** | University department registry |
| **Course** | Academic course catalog |
| **Notification** | In-app notification documents (recipient, type, title, message, grievance ref) |
| **AuditLog** | Tamper-evident audit trail with action, actor, target, metadata |
| **ApprovalRequest** | Admin signup approval workflow |
| **ComplianceRequest** | Compliance/data-export requests |
| **SecurityEvent** | Security incidents (lockouts, suspicious logins) |
| **BackupStatus** | Backup job status records |
| **LandingPageConfig** | Per-role customizable landing page content |
| **SiteConfig** | Global singleton config: SLA matrix, security settings, notification policies, role templates, message templates, audit retention |
| **ComplaintType** | Lightweight complaint type (stub, likely deprecated) |

### 3.4 Middleware Stack

| File | Role |
|---|---|
| `authMiddleware.js` | JWT extraction (Bearer header OR httpOnly cookie), User/Admin dual-lookup, `signAccessToken`, `signRefreshToken`, `setAuthCookies`, `clearAuthCookies`, `authorize()` role check |
| `rbac.js` | Permission-based access control; `rolePermissions` map + `authorizePermission()` middleware; superadmin gets `"*"` wildcard |
| `guards.js` | Route-level guard helpers (department scope enforcement) |
| `rateLimiters.js` | `express-rate-limit` — `apiLimiter` applied to all protected routes |
| `stepUp.js` | Step-up authentication for sensitive operations (OTP-gated) |
| `upload.js` | Multer config for grievance attachments |
| `userUploads.js` | Multer config for user ID-card uploads |
| `errorHandler.js` | Central error handler — maps ValidationError, MulterError, MongoServerError (11000), CastError, JWT errors to proper HTTP codes. Strips stack traces in production. |

### 3.5 Auth Flow

```
Login request
  → validate credentials (bcrypt.compare)
  → signAccessToken (15m expiry, HS256)
  → signRefreshToken (7d expiry, random jti for rotation)
  → setAuthCookies (httpOnly, secure in prod, sameSite=lax)
  → return { user, accessToken } in body

Protected request
  → extractToken (Bearer header > cookie fallback)
  → jwt.verify with ACCESS_TOKEN_SECRET
  → User.findById (primary) or Admin.findById (legacy fallback)
  → req.user = user, req.role = user.role

Token refresh
  → POST /api/auth/refresh
  → reads httpOnly refresh cookie
  → verifies with REFRESH_TOKEN_SECRET
  → issues new access + refresh token pair
```

### 3.6 SLA Escalation Job (`slaEscalationJob.js`)

- Runs every **30 minutes** via `node-cron`
- Finds all non-terminal, non-escalated grievances where `slaDeadline < now`
- Marks them `status: "Escalated"`, `isEscalated: true`, appends to `timeline[]`
- Creates `Notification` documents for: all active superadmins, the submitting student, and the assigned admin
- Creates an `AuditLog` record for each auto-escalation
- Non-blocking: errors are caught and logged without crashing the server

### 3.7 Redis Cache (`utils/cache.js`)

- **Optional** — if `REDIS_URL` is not set, all cache calls are no-ops (non-fatal)
- `getCache`, `setCache`, `delCache` (SCAN-based, not KEYS — avoids O(N) blocking)
- Used primarily for caching report/dashboard aggregations

