## 4. Frontend — Deep Dive

### 4.1 Technology Stack
- **React 19**, **React Router v7**, **Vite 7**
- **Tailwind CSS v4** (via PostCSS)
- **Lucide React** for icons
- **Recharts / react-chartjs-2** for analytics charts
- **Axios** for HTTP with in-memory token management
- **react-hot-toast / react-toastify** for notifications

### 4.2 Routing Architecture (`AppRoutes.jsx`)

Three protected route groups using `<ProtectedRoute allowedRoles={[...]}>`:

```
Public routes (in PublicRoute wrapper):
  /                     LandingPage
  /login                User Login
  /signup               User Signup
  /forgot-password      ForgotPassword
  /reset-password       ResetPassword
  /admin                AdminLandingPage
  /admin/login          AdminLogin
  /superadmin           SuperAdminLandingPage
  /superadmin/login     SuperAdminLogin

Student routes (role: "student"):
  /dashboard            Dashboard
  /submit-grievance     CreateGrievance
  /my-drafts            MyDrafts
  /my-grievances        MyGrievances
  /grievance/:id        TrackGrievance (detail)
  /track-grievance      TrackGrievance (search)
  /notifications        NotificationsPage
  /profile              Profile

Admin routes (role: "admin"):
  /admin/dashboard       AdminDashboard
  /admin/grievances      AdminGrievances
  /admin/pending         PendingGrievances
  /admin/resolved        AdminGrievances (fixedStatus="Resolved")
  /admin/escalated       AdminGrievances (fixedStatus="Escalated")
  /admin/grievance/:id   AdminGrievanceDetails
  /admin/notifications   NotificationsPage
  /admin/profile         AdminProfile

SuperAdmin routes (role: "superadmin"):
  /superadmin/dashboard        SuperAdminDashboard
  /superadmin/admins           AllAdmins
  /superadmin/pending-admins   PendingAdmins
  /superadmin/departments      ManageDepartments
  /superadmin/courses          ManageCourses
  /superadmin/categories       ComplaintTypes
  /superadmin/landing-editor   LandingEditor
  /superadmin/reports          SuperAdminReports
  /superadmin/users            SuperAdminUsers
  /superadmin/settings         SuperAdminSettings
  /superadmin/control-center   SuperAdminControlCenter
  /superadmin/audit-logs       AuditLogs
  /superadmin/notifications    NotificationsPage
  /superadmin/profile          AdminProfile
  /superadmin/grievance/:id    AdminGrievanceDetails
```

### 4.3 State Management

| Layer | Mechanism |
|---|---|
| Auth state | `AuthContext` / `AuthProvider` — stores `authUser`, `accessToken`, `loading`, `isAuthenticated`; methods: `loginStudent`, `loginAdmin`, `loginSuperAdmin`, `registerUser`, `logout`, `updateAuthUser` |
| Token storage | **In-memory only** (`_memToken` in axiosInstance.js) — never localStorage. Refresh cookie is httpOnly. |
| Session restore | On mount, `AuthProvider` calls `POST /api/auth/refresh` to restore session from httpOnly cookie |
| Visibility revalidation | On `pageshow` and `visibilitychange` events, re-calls `/api/auth/refresh` to detect stale sessions |
| Notifications | `NotificationContext` + `useNotifications` hook — polls/fetches unread count |

### 4.4 HTTP Client (`axiosInstance.js`)

- Base URL: `VITE_API_URL/api` (env) or `/api` (Vite proxy in dev)
- Request interceptor: injects `Authorization: Bearer <memToken>` if token exists
- Response interceptor: on 401, triggers a single refresh attempt; queues concurrent failed requests; retries after refresh; prevents refresh loops via `_retry` flag and `skipAuthRefresh` config option

### 4.5 Component Structure

```
components/
  common/
    AppLayout.jsx         — Unified sidebar + header shell for all 3 roles
    AuthenticatedImage    — Renders protected images using auth headers
    BrandMark             — University logo/initials fallback
    EmptyState            — Empty list placeholder
    RouteTracker          — Analytics/route change tracking
    Skeleton              — Loading placeholder
    StepUpModal           — OTP challenge dialog for sensitive actions
  ui/
    Badge, Button, Card, Input, Modal  — Primitive design system
  landing/                — Landing page section components
  protected/
    ProtectedRoute.jsx    — Role-based route guard
    PublicRoute.jsx       — Redirects authenticated users away from public pages
```

### 4.6 Page Inventory

**Student (8 pages):**
- `Dashboard` — Stats overview, recent grievances
- `CreateGrievance` — Multi-step submission form with file uploads
- `MyGrievances` — List with filtering
- `MyDrafts` — Draft grievances
- `TrackGrievance` — Timeline view with comments
- `Profile` — User profile editing, ID card upload
- `Login`, `Signup`

**Admin (7 pages):**
- `AdminDashboard` — Dept-scoped stats and charts
- `AdminGrievances` — Filterable grievance list (shared with Pending/Resolved/Escalated views via `fixedStatus` prop)
- `AdminGrievanceDetails` — Full grievance detail + status update + comment
- `AdminProfile` — Profile management
- `AdminLogin`, `AdminAbout`, `PendingGrievances`

**SuperAdmin (13 pages):**
- `SuperAdminDashboard` — Platform-wide analytics
- `AllAdmins` — Admin management (CRUD, approve/reject)
- `PendingAdmins` — Admin signup approvals
- `ManageDepartments` — Department CRUD
- `ManageCourses` — Course CRUD
- `ComplaintTypes` — Category management
- `LandingEditor` — Visual landing page configurator
- `SuperAdminReports` — Report generation (CSV/PDF)
- `SuperAdminUsers` — User lifecycle management
- `SuperAdminSettings` — Security config, SLA matrix
- `SuperAdminControlCenter` — Platform health, backup, compliance
- `AuditLogs` — Filterable audit trail viewer
- `SuperAdminLogin`

