## 5. Security Design

| Concern | Implementation |
|---|---|
| Password hashing | bcrypt, 12 rounds (User model), 10 rounds (Admin model) |
| JWT | HS256, short-lived access tokens (15m), long-lived refresh tokens (7d) with random `jti` |
| Token storage | Access token in-memory only; refresh token in httpOnly cookie |
| CSRF protection | Prod-only: validates `Origin`/`Referer` against allowed origins for cookie-authenticated mutation requests |
| CORS | Whitelist via `ALLOWED_ORIGINS` env var |
| Content Security Policy | Helmet + strict CSP in production |
| NoSQL injection | `express-mongo-sanitize` |
| HTTP param pollution | `hpp` middleware |
| Rate limiting | `express-rate-limit` on all protected route groups |
| Path traversal | Explicit checks on upload file serving (`..` and `path.isAbsolute` guards) |
| Account lockout | `loginAttempts` + `lockUntil` fields on User; configurable via SiteConfig |
| Step-up auth | OTP-gated high-privilege actions (configurable window via SiteConfig) |
| RBAC | Role hierarchy (student < admin < superadmin) + per-permission `authorizePermission()` |
| Audit trail | `AuditLog` model; SLA auto-escalation always creates audit records |

